  "response_text": "The Gini coefficient for healthy livestock starts at 0.0 at timestep 1 and rises steadily to 0.0726 by timestep 100, with an overall mean of 0.0302 and a standard deviation of 0.0239. The increase is significant, as confirmed by rolling Mann-Kendall tests across all time windows (tau=1.0, p=0.000, slope=0.001). The trajectory shows an inflection around timestep 51, where the rate of increase accelerates, and another at timestep 71, with the final value reaching its peak at timestep 100. Oscillations are observed in the range of timesteps 78 to 93, though the trend remains strongly upward. This trend suggests that inequality in healthy livestock holdings among households grows consistently over time, becoming most pronounced in the later stages of the simulation. For decision makers, this indicates that without intervention, disparities in livestock health outcomes will naturally widen, potentially undermining community resilience and equitable development."
}

